==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Owlet
<hw>Owl"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>owl</ets>. Cf. <er>Howlet</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
small owl; especially, the European species (<spn>Athene noctua</spn>),
and the California flammulated owlet (<spn>Megascops
flammeolus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Owlet moth</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any noctuid
moth.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Owl-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
